review_summary: Great pattern makes super cute dresses
review_text: I sewed the no sleeve and 3/4 sleeve versions of this pattern for my daughter.  Overall the pattern instructions were easy to follow, but the bodice portion took a little while to figure out.  My daughter is very tiny - typically a size 0 - and I cut the fabric using the guidelines for a size 8.  Be careful to look at the measurements before cutting.  I could have finished the dress in one day, it was that easy.  This was a great value for the money and the dress cost a lot less to make than to purchase, and it fit her perfectly.  She got multiple compliments the first day she wore it.
product_title: Simplicity Pattern 1360 Misses' Maternity Knit Dress or Mini Dress, K5 (8-10-12-14-16)

review_summary: I like the paper weight in this pad - not cheap ...
review_text:
I like the paper weight in this pad - not cheap 34lb paper.  There is a lot of 'ruled paper' on the back, so what you see on the front cover is it - but these would probably be best used as journaling cards with all the ruled paper designs on the back of the DSP sheets.

For making cards, I have started using 6x6 pads only now.  The design is sized much smaller so the scale of the design fits the size of the card.  And the cost is great.  If I buy 12x12 pads now, I'm careful to buy patterns that are solid across the whole sheet - I do not want to make cards with a scrapbooking DSP sheet.  I can do it, but I would rather have the consistent solid pattern across the whole sheet instead of having to cut the page up in a way to work around the lopsided/huge focal point on a scrapbooking page.
